article.headline: James Madison gets past Richmond 51-46
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Hari Hall scored 12 points and Yohanny Dalembert had 10 to lead James Madison to a 51-46 win over Richmond on Sunday. Andre Nation's basket gave James Madison a 48-44 lead with 39 seconds left. Richmond's Trey Davis hit two free throws to pull within two points, but James Madison's Jackson Kent converted a pair and Ron Curry made 1 of 2 to close out the game. Kent added nine points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help James Madison (6-2) hold a 39-27 advantage on the glass. Kendall Anthony led Richmond (3-4) with 16 points. It was a defensive battle as both teams shot under 40 percent from the field and committed 13 turnovers apiece. Richmond hit seven of its 25 3-pointers and James Madison was just 1 of 13. James Madison is undefeated in its six homes games with away loses to No. 7 Virginia and No. 14 Ohio State.
